docs.snippet: Foreign exchange market passed through one of its dullest weeks in months. Business was extremely light and in the main represented balancing of accounts with no extended interest on either side of the market.

docs.lead_paragraph: Boris Ivkov of Yugoslavia and Miguel Najdorf of Argentina won in the international chess masters tournament at Mar del Plata yesterday, according to a report from Buenos Aires. As a result, Ivkov, with 11--3, maintained his half-point lead over Najdorf in the fourteenth and semi-final round.

docs.snippet: OKLAHOMA CITY, April 2 (AP)--Louise Suggs of Georgia shot a 3-under-par 74 to increase her lead in the second round of the $5,000 Oklahoma City women's open golf tournament.
